Sentencas: The effects of sintering temperature on the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode LSCF-SDCC are discussed in this paper.
Titulo: Effects of Sintering Temperature on the Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) composite cathode LSCF-SDCC

Sentencas: An LSCF-SDCC composite cathode was prepared at 50: 50 weights percentage ratios.
Titulo: Effects of Sintering Temperature on the Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) composite cathode LSCF-SDCC

Sentencas: The LSCF-SDCC film was fabricated through electrophoretic deposition (EPD) method.
Titulo: Effects of Sintering Temperature on the Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) composite cathode LSCF-SDCC

Sentencas: EPD was conducted on both sides of the SDCC substrate to produce a symmetrical cell.
Titulo: Effects of Sintering Temperature on the Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) composite cathode LSCF-SDCC

Sentencas: The symmetrical cell was subjected to different sintering temperatures (550 degrees C to 750 degrees C) before undergoing microstructure analysis and an electrochemical performance test.
Titulo: Effects of Sintering Temperature on the Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) composite cathode LSCF-SDCC

Sentencas: The effects of sintering temperature change on film surface porosity were first investigated by energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy, field emission scanning electron microscopy and ImageJ analysis.
Titulo: Effects of Sintering Temperature on the Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) composite cathode LSCF-SDCC

Sentencas: Then, the relation of polarisation resistance, Rp, with the sintering temperatures was established through electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Effects of Sintering Temperature on the Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) composite cathode LSCF-SDCC

Sentencas: LSCF-SDCC that was sintered at 600 degrees C exhibited the lowest Rp value of 0.68 Omega when operated at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Effects of Sintering Temperature on the Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) composite cathode LSCF-SDCC

Sentencas: The results showed that sintering temperature in the range of 550 degrees C to 650 degrees C is the best sintering temperature to produce a high-performance LSCF-SDCC composite cathode.
Titulo: Effects of Sintering Temperature on the Electrochemical Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) composite cathode LSCF-SDCC
